# Generated Output — Do Not Edit

**Never** fix bugs, lint, or type errors by hand-editing generated or bundled artifacts. Change the **source** (generator, DSL, core2ai, or bundle input), then rebuild and regenerate.

## Do not edit (fix upstream instead)

| Path | Fix in |
|------|--------|
| `packages/extension/demos/generated/tools/**` | `packages/cli/src/generator/**` → `npm run build`, `npm run generate:all` |
| `packages/extension/demos/generated/cli/mcp-serve.mjs` | `npm run bundle:mcp-runtime`, then `npm run generate:all` (or core2ai pin refresh first) |
| `packages/cli/resources/mcp-serve-emitted.mjs` | `npm run bundle:mcp-runtime` after `@core2ai/core/mcp-host` is current |
| `node_modules/@core2ai/core/**` | Tag + `npm run core2ai:refresh-pin`, then bundle + generate |

Do **not** run `eslint --fix` on generated files. Do **not** use manual `cp` into `generated/**` or `node_modules` as a permanent fix.

## Allowed to edit (not generator output)

- Demo DSL: `packages/extension/demos/*.db2ai`
- Hand-written auth stubs: `packages/extension/demos/src/auth/**`
- Demo scripts, compose, README, env templates under `packages/extension/demos/` (excluding `generated/**`)

Regenerated `generated/**` files may be **committed** after a generator or DSL change — that is output of the pipeline, not a manual patch.

## Verification

After generator changes, follow [codegen-generated-quality.mdc](./codegen-generated-quality.mdc). After core2ai or MCP-host changes, follow [core2ai-consumer-impact.mdc](./core2ai-consumer-impact.mdc).
